            "html": "Giant wolverines grow to the approximate size of horses and claim even more expansive territories than their more diminutive wolverine cousins. While a smaller wolverine will defend its prey from armed humanoids, a giant wolverine is unafraid to stalk and kill such creatures.<br/><br/><b><u><a aonid=\"5\" game-obj=\"Skills\" general=\"true\">Recall Knowledge - Animal</a></u> (<u><a aonid=\"10\" game-obj=\"Skills\">Nature</a></u>)</b>: DC 19"
        },
        {
            "name": "Wolverine",
            "type": "section",
            "sections": [
                {
                    "name": "Territorial Beasts",
                    "type": "section",
                    "sources": [
                        {
                            "type": "source",
                            "name": "Bestiary 2",
                            "link": {
                                "type": "link",
                                "name": "Bestiary 2 pg. 295",
                                "alt": "Bestiary 2 pg. 295",
                                "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq022yq"
                            },
                            "page": 295,
                            "errata": {
                                "type": "link",
                                "name": "2.0",
                                "alt": "2.0",
                                "game-obj": "Sources",
                                "aonid": 32
                            }
                        }
                    ],
                    "subtype": "sidebar",
                    "sidebar_type": "additional_lore",
                    "sidebar_heading": "Additional Lore",
                    "image": {
                        "type": "image",
                        "name": "Additional Lore",
                        "image": "Sidebar_2_AdditionalLore.png"
                    },
                    "html": "Wolverines are territorial animals and fiercely defend their kills, even from larger predators or when they're outnumbered. They claim wide swaths of forests or frozen tundra as their territory, marking it with a pungent odor that serves as a warning to those who recognize the smell. Wolverines have voracious appetites and tend to aggressively devour their food with reckless abandon."
                }
            ],
            "sources": [
                {
                    "type": "source",
                    "name": "Bestiary 2",
                    "link": {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Bestiary 2 pg. 295",
                        "alt": "Bestiary 2 pg. 295",
                        "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq022yq"
                    },
                    "page": 295,
                    "errata": {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "2.0",
                        "alt": "2.0",
                        "game-obj": "Sources",
                        "aonid": 32
                    }
                }
            ],
            "html": "Few creatures in the natural world can compare in ferocity to an angry wolverine."
        }
    ],
